    <thetext>I think this is of high importance. Word and grapheme boundary analysis are things that we do a fair amount of in our applications (for features such as dictionary lookup, text highlighting that is scripted, etc.). For some languages, such as JP, CN, Thai, etc., this can&apos;t be done trivially and requires a large data set to do a high quality job of. There exist some smaller, statistically based implementations, but these are not accurate enough for our needs.</thetext>
